Global Procurement Initiative: Energy Procurement Specialist Technical Assistance

The Global Procurement Initiative: Procurement Assistance Program for Thailand is a national-level Program aimed to train Thai procurement officials on international best practices in procurement to obtain the greatest value for money for public investments. The Procurement Assistance Program is made up of four components: (1) A Virtual Training Series composed of up to 10 webinars; (2) a three day In-Country Workshop in Bangkok; (3) a 12-13-calendar day Study Tour to the United States for public procurement leaders; and (4) a Virtual Forum to bring together all participants from the respective training activities for a discussion on change management. The goal of the Program is to build upon technical skills required to be able to procure infrastructure utilizing value-based procurement mechanisms and life-cycle cost analysis.

This Life-Cycle Cost Analysis (LCCA) Curriculum Platform Maintenance and Supplemental Training Contract provides ongoing technical services including the continued hosting and maintenance of the LCCA web-based course developed under a previous contract as well as supplemental live-training support on LCCA. The LCCA web-based course is utilized to train public procurement practitioners on how to conduct life-cycle cost analyses in government procurements.

This activity funds a sole-source contract for Supply Chain Vision, Inc. to continue to host and maintain the Life Cycle Cost Analysis (LCCA) web-based course developed under a previous contract. The Contractor will be responsible for hosting and maintaining the online course and applying necessary changes to the curriculum for a period of one year plus four option years, if exercised. The LCCA web-based course is utilized to train procurement practitioners in value-based procurement methods under the Global Procurement Initiative: Understanding Best Value (GPI). This requests authorization to proceed with the optional task for supplemental live trainings under the Life-Cycle Cost Analysis Curriculum Platform Maintenance and Supplemental Training Contract and provides two 60-minute webinars to two current partner countries under the Global Procurement Initiative: Understanding Best Value (GPI). The requested authorization allows Supply Chain Visions, Inc., the Contractor currently providing services under this Contract, to develop and deliver the two 60-minute webinars to two current GPI partner countries.
